     <h3>The Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education</h3>
     <h5>Ministry of Education</h5>
     <p>Under this scheme, students with disabilities and children from economically weaker families get free access to compulsory elementary education and school.</p>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row" id="row2">
    <h4>Benifits :</h4>
    <p>Children got the right to receive free elementary education. This means that no child has to pay any kind of charges or fee to complete education up to elementary level. The RTE act also aims at the development of a curriculum that makes sure the child receives the benefit of all-round development, building their knowledge, talent, and potential.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="row" id="row2">
    <h4>Application Procedure :</h4>
    <ul>
     <li>Check Schools in the Neighborhood.</li>
     <li>The first step to applying for schools under the RTE quota is to find eligible schools in your neighbourhood.</li>
     <li>Using the quota should log onto the government portal and fill the document provided. Once you fill the form, print it.</li>
     <li>Submit the form with the relevant documents to the relevant authorities in the school of your choice.</li>

   </ul>  
    
    </div>
    <div class="row" id="row2">
    <h4>Documents Required :</h4>
    <ul>
     <li>Child ID such as adhar card,passport,birth certificate.</li>
     <li>Caste certificate</li>
     <li>Income certificate from the Revenue Department of India.</li>
     <li>Photographs of the child.</li>
     <li>If the child is an orphan, the death certificate of both parents must be produced.</li>
     
   </ul>  
    
